transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop Store Management tutorial series.
In this video we will learn about how to create duplicate templates.
The duplicate template feature allows the admin to assign templates of one product to similar products with the same sizes in bulk.
From the master template, you can create a new version template with a resize option for products with similar bleed, width and height.
Let's have a look at the steps to create and manage duplicate templates.
From the admin panel.
Go to the Templates section and then click on the Duplicate Templates menu.
In this section, we have 3 features, Add Duplicate Templates, Remove Duplicate Templates and Duplicate the templates with resize.
So let's first talk about how we can add duplicate templates.
So we are taking a business card for which we will assign templates in bulk.
Let's verify the Browse design page for this product on the front end.
As you can see, we don't have any template for this product.
Let's add templates for this product using the Duplicate Templates feature.
So moving back to the Add Duplicate Templates section here, select the user type and choose the product of which you want to copy the templates.
Once you select the product, a list of templates will appear below with a checkbox for the selection.
Here you can see the number of PDF block templates, master templates and product templates assigned to the selected product.
Select the templates that you want to copy in the Duplicate Products section.
A list of products with the same bleed size will appear.
You can select products to which you want to assign the templates in bulk, eventually saving time in creating templates.
Save the changes.
Now when you check the browse design page for the same product, you can see the templates are now displayed.
So in this way you can duplicate templates from existing products to a new product in bulk.
If you want to remove the templates from any product, you can do so with the Remove duplicate template feature.
Here you can search for the product from which you want to remove the duplicated templates.
Let's select the same business card product here to which we assigned templates.
Then select the product from the list, check all the check boxes and just click on save.
Once you save it, the duplicated templates will be removed from the selected products on the front end.
When you refresh the page again, you can see all the templates are removed.
Let's talk about duplicate templates with the resize feature now in this section.
When you duplicate any template, it will either resize the existing templates and assign them to the new product size or it will create new versions depending on the configuration.
To see the steps, you first need to define the template type.
You can select from Product Templates or Master Templates.
When you select master templates, the existing templates can only be resized.
And when you select product templates then you have an option for the resize where you can decide if you want to resize the existing templates or create a new template or version.
Let's select the second option and then select the product type.
Now it is time to select the source product from which you will assign the template.
The below space will display the number of templates assigned to the product.
Here you will not have the option to select the templates.
Now select the new product to which all these templates will be assigned.
If you have selected the resize option then all these templates will be resized and moved to the new product.
And if you have opted to create new templates then new templates with defined sizes will be created and assigned to the product.
And there you have it.
This was all about how you can create remove the duplicate templates and create duplicate templates with the resize option.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
